      Omnidirectional <br class="br-mobile" /> Ultra-<br
        class="br-tablet"
      />wide-angle <br class="br-desktop br-mobile" /> Scanning
    </h2>
    <p class="paragraph-1">
      The L2 is a revolutionary bionic 4D laser radar designed to accelerate the
      era of mobile intelligence. It achieves a superior field of view with 360°
      circumferential scanning and 96° vertical scanning, utilizing
      non-repetitive scanning technology to generate high-precision,
      high-density point cloud data. This capability enables photograph-level
      scanning effects for detailed environment mapping.
    </p>
    <div class="media-wrapper">
      <video playsinline muted loop preload="metadata" class="media">
        <source src="/videos/perception/1.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
      </video>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="simple-section full-desktop full-tablet align-end-desktop">
    <h2 class="h1">
      Robust Performance in <br /> Extreme Conditions
    </h2>
    <p class="paragraph-1">
      Engineered for reliability, the L2 features Anti-glare Capability of over
      100Klux. This means it can effectively resist the interference of both
      indoor ambient light and outdoor strong sunlight, achieving stable ranging
      and high-precision mapping even under bright outdoor conditions. Its
      compact size and low weight make it easy to integrate into any mobile
      platform.
    </p>
    <div class="media-wrapper">
      <video playsinline muted loop preload="metadata" class="media">
        <source src="/videos/perception/2.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
      </video>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="simple-section full-desktop full-tablet">
    <h2 class="h1">
      Essential for SLAM and <br /> Autonomous <br class="br-mobile" /> Navigation
    </h2>
    <p class="paragraph-1">
      The L2 provides a complete open-source SLAM solution, crucial for robot
      positioning and autonomous navigation. Its minimal near blind spot of
      0.05m and high measurement accuracy of ± 2.0cm ensure that robots can
      quickly and accurately obtain the 3D structural information of their
      environment, expanding functions such as whole-house cleaning,
      organization, and complex industrial logistics.
    </p>
    <div class="media-wrapper">
      <video playsinline muted loop preload="metadata" class="media">
        <source src="/videos/perception/3.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
      </video>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="simple-section full-desktop full-tablet align-end-desktop">
    <h2 class="h1">4D Data Output</h2>
    <p class="paragraph-1">
      The L2 outputs 4D data, which includes 3D position data plus 1D grayscale
      information. This additional dimension enriches the point cloud, providing
      valuable context for object recognition and material differentiation,
      further enhancing the robot's ability to understand and interact with its
      environment.
    </p>
    <div class="media-wrapper">
      <video playsinline muted loop preload="metadata" class="media">
        <source src="/videos/perception/4.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
      </video>
    </div>
  </section>
